The paper deals with stochastic processes on networks, which is a topic that can fall under several sub-categories in computer science. "cs.SI" (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper specifically mentions the spread of computer viruses, rumors, and infectious diseases on networks. "cs.SY" (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the dynamics of stochastic spreading processes. "cs.NI" (Networking and Internet Architecture) is another possible category as the paper deals with spreading processes on complex networks. "cs.DS" (Data Structures and Algorithms) and "cs.MA" (Multiagent Systems) are also possible categories as the paper proposes a novel simulation approach that combines event-based simulation and rejection sampling.
